@celia_soto_art okay but I truly don’t think that something so sacred is made to be a public thing ... that’s what makes it disgusting.

@nina_womanempowers True... But as society treats menstruation as something to be hidden or ashamed of, it is clear that the sacredness is not respected. That is why I show publicly feminine, menstruation, yoni art. How society, in the whole world, treats its women 'n girls is not beautiful yet. So we need to make our voices heard: as women and men, together. This is what I do here, one of so many other brave women...🌊

@celia_soto_art I believe that preserving the privacy of a woman is more important than gaining social recognition and radically mass social approval of such a private matter. Self esteem comes within not from outside ourselves - no matter how much you want women to love their menstruation cycle and embrace it with respect we should allow women to feel the way they wish of course with complete knowledge of why you think it’s so incredible.
